cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use ci-churn in a paper, retro, or engineering-metrics blog post, cite it as follows."
title: "ci-churn: CI churn detection for pull requests"
abstract: >-
  ci-churn reads a pull request's commits and GitHub Actions run durations,
  classifies commits as feature, review-fix, or ci-fix, and reports the
  CI-compute burned on avoidable retry pushes. Ships as an agent skill
  (SKILL.md) compatible with Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Gemini CLI, and pi.
type: software
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/gaia-research/skill-ci-churn"
url: "https://github.com/gaia-research/skill-ci-churn#readme"
keywords:
  - ci-churn
  - flaky-tests
  - github-actions
  - pipeline-analytics
  - agent-skill
  - claude-code
  - anthropic
  - developer-tools
authors:
